oks at the intimate realities of Filipinas, Chinese women, and U.S. men corresponding in hopes of finding a suitable marriage partner. Through the experiences of those engaged in pen pal relationships-their stories of love, romance, migration, and long-distance dating-this book conveys the richness and dignity of women's and men's choices without reducing these correspondents to calculating opportunists or naive romantics. Attentive to the structural, cultural, and personal factors that prompt women and men to seek marriage partners abroad, Romance on a Global Stage questions the dichotomies so frequently drawn between structure and agency, and between global and local levels of analysis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAgences matrimonialesxÉtats-Unis. 0aAsiansxUnited States. 0aAsianszUnited States. 0aAsiatiquesxÉtats-Unis. 0aCorrespondance internationalexÉtats-Unis. 0aIntercountry marriagexUnited States. 0aIntercountry marriagezUnited States. 0aInternational correspondencexSocial aspects. 0aMail order bridesxUnited States. 0aMail order brideszUnited States. 0aMariage interethniquexÉtats-Unis. 0aMariage par correspondancexÉtats-Unis. 0aMarriage brokeragexUnited States. 0aMarriage brokeragezUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937222423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520937222.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles